    {
        "user": "U081Z9041A5",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1740441770.365759",
        "client_msg_id": "be01c9c6-5225-488a-80fa-a64418eb9877",
        "text": "That is somwhere between \"that's how it is always been\" and \"but it's never been phrased that way\".  The aim to have CRAN work 'at any point in time\" so a _consistent snapshot_ should work too.   And of course, CRAN _per se_ has no 'history' or 'download as-of' mechanism.\n\nBut that is what MRAN did (snapshot by date) and what <http:\/\/p3m.dev|p3m.dev> now does.  So there is a pretty long (if informal) history of relying on this.",
